rt": "4188.573","u": "He came to me into the lager driving the tank."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4190.901","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4192.001","u": "And purposely searched me out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4194.048","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4195.633","u": "And I didn&#39;t...he has...he has treated me...I have no words! And after that time I didn&#39;t see him any more because, naturally, he went on."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4204.199","u": "What is his name?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4205.769","u": "What?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4206.294","u": "What is the name?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4207.697","u": "The name I don&#39;t know."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4208.562","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4213.695","u": "I went back to the lager I had...hungry I wasn&#39;t any more. I already had stuffed myself with chocolate, with other things. I came into the lager. There were lot of sick people who couldn&#39;t...couldn&#39;t, alas, walk by themselves, who waited for somebody to bring them something. So there I...I had a lot of things. I distributed to them cigarettes- -This in our lager was an especially important article which...it was very seldom that one came across cigarettes. If one did come across cigarettes... If one did come across...they were dried leaves from trees; And this, one smoked. And then came...the American began to come into the camp. After two days we began to receive dinner. This was still a day before. I got up, and I knew that bread I didn&#39;t receive from the American when I met the tank, but I knew that bread I will receive somewhere else, from a German who is in the lager. So I went up to the one who pulled me out from that...out from the storeroom upstairs [?]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4288.331","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4288.914","u": "I had already seen him..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4290.649","u": "How was that?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4292.090","u": "He was a prisoner too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4292.897","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4293.800","u": "I go up to him and stopped before him, and begin to look at him so. I ask him, &#39;Do you recognize me, or don&#39;t you recognize me?&#39; He said, &#39;No, I do not recognize you.&#39;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4307.459","u": "He was a German?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4308.719","u": "A German. That gypsy who..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4310.871","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4311.007","u": "...had pulled me out of the storeroom. So I say, &#39;You don&#39;t know me? Now I am going to settle with you. Wait!&#39; And say to him, &#39;I am the one whom you have taken out from the storeroom.&#39; He became shocked and pale, and he did not know what to answer. He was just in the middle of eating, so he gave me bread. So I say, &#39;No, not the bread I mean. Now I want to settle with you for that, because you took me out from the store- room. I begged you like a child a year old, that you should let me go. I am one, left by myself.&#39; He says, &#39;What do you want to do to me? Do what you want with me.&#39; And so, first of all I am hungry, so I took from him the bread."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4352.673","u": "Why? The Americans were already there."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4355.647","u": "For bread I was hungry. The Americans were not yet in the lager."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4359.096","u": "Oh."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4359.375","u": "They couldn&#39;t come into the camp because, the...the...the soldiers who walked on foot..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4365.485","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4366.469","u": "...that means, they who made the...who began to make the arrangements were not yet there."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4369.784","u": "But you said the tank came in."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4372.628","u": "The tank drove in only two days later."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4375.030","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4376.462","u": "The tank first drove in two days later."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4377.993","u": "But the tank with whom you..."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4379.735","u": "The one I talked with, he drove on..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4381.562","u": "Oh."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4381.753","u": "...and only two days later..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4381.964","u": "Oh, later..."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4382.379","u": "...he said he will come to me, and two days later he came."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4385.646","u": "Hm. All right. Nu?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4388.970","u": "So I say, &#39;Now I am letting you go, but, in a few days I shall find you.&#39; I should have settled with him then and there because I searched for him later. In a few days he was not in the lager any more. That I could not help."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4433.017","u": "One moment..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4434.499","u": "[In English] This is Mendel Herskovitz. [spool has become very noisy.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4439.749","u": "[In Yiddish] What does this picture remind you of?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4443.409","u": "This picture can remind me of only one thing."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4443.409","u": "What is that?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4448.307","u": "How father was standing near a dying son, or a son was standing near a dying father, or a brother near a brother."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4460.217","u": "And what doe this picture remind you of? [Aside:] This is #18."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4482.964","u": "[Pause.] The moment when we stood up to the knees in snow, shivering from the cold. We could stand like this for five [?] hours, on an appell until the block elder would decide to let us inside."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4501.768","u": "And..."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4502.620","u": "And not one [many] perished at such an appell. About [?] women too..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4513.107","u": "[Not clear.] Yes?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4514.650","u": "...because no women were with us in the lager. But I can only imagine, according to what I see here. I can imagine how I was running with a pair of ghostly eyes and stared in front of me...until I was saved [?] by the liberation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4531.450","u": "And what is this?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4534.318","u": "Here I can only remind myself of childhood years. How I sat at our own table."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4538.806","u": "What?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4540.153","u": "The childhood years. How I sat at our own table."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4543.888","u": "[Aside:] Number one. And what is this?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4555.706","u": "Country place at home where we often went."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4562.305","u": "That was number two. Yes, one moment. Now number three, BM."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4586.931","u": "[Pause.] A sick prisoner and a hungry one, without hope."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4591.434","u": "Hm. Well Mendel..."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4596.078","u": "That is all?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4596.747","u": "That was good. We have learned a lot from your story. We have heard some in America during the war, but no matter how much one hears, it is not enough."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4612.026","u": "I do not that much of...I do not have that much in me of the poetical power that I should be able to relate everything."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4619.695","u": "One does not need poetical powers..."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4622.351","u": "I cannot..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4623.658","u": "...to tell in simple words."},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4627.053","u": "It is....How much one can...a person simply cannot imagine it, and a writer cannot describe it, every moment separately that one...what the one went through and what he saw that others went through. That on an evening a German could come in when we sat and we ate the soup. He could come in, distribute cigarettes, and suddenly take out the pistol and begin shooting those who were sitting. He could [words not clear]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4658.232","u": "Did you yourself see that?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4660.118","u": "I saw that too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4661.592","u": "Where was that?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4662.139","u": "The bullet by chance did not hit me."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4664.431","u": "What?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4665.079","u": "The bullet by chance did not hit me. Surely I saw it."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4667.295","u": "You saw it. Where was that?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4670.344","u": "This was in the lager. [Pause.] In Dachau."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4682.197","u": "Were you in Dachau?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4683.532","u": "What?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4684.053","u": "Have you been in Dachau?"},    {"who": "Mendel Herskovitz", "start": "4684.929","u": "I was 